==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: anastatic
<hw>an`a*stat"ic</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n"⟦adot⟧*st⟦asl⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'ana`</grk> up + <grk>ista`nai</grk> to
make to stand: cf. <grk>statiko`s</grk> causing to stand.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to a process or a style of printing from characters in
relief on zinc plates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>In this process the letterpress, engraving, or design of any
kind is transferred to a zinc plate; the parts not covered with ink are
eaten out, leaving a facsimile in relief to be printed from.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anastatica</ent>⟦br⟧
